## Design Secure Access to AWS Resources

Knowledge of
- Access Controls and management across multiple accounts
- AWS federated access and Identity Services ( for exampe, AWS identity and Access Management, AWS SSO)
- AWS global infrastructure
- AWS Security Best practices
- AWS shard responsibility model

Skills in:
- Applying AWS Security best practices to IAM users and root users (e.g. MFA)
- Designing flexible autorization model that includes IAM users, groups, roles and policy
- Designing a role-based access control strategy (e.g. AWS STS, role switching, cross-account access)
- Designing a security strategy for multiple AES accounts (AWS Control Tower, SCPs)
- Determining the appropriate use of resoure policies for AWS services
- Determining when to federate a directory service with IAM roles

## Design Secure workloads and applications

Knowledge of
- Application configuration and credentials security
- AWS service endpoints
- Control ports, protocols, and netowrk traffic on AWS
- secure application access
- security serices with apropriate use cases (e.g Amazon Cognito, GuardDuty, Macie)
- Threat Vectors external to AWS (e.g. DDoS, SQL injection)

Skills in:
- Designing VPC architectures with security components (e.g. security groups, route tables, network ACLS, NAT Gateway)
- Determining network segmentatin strategies (e.g. AWS Shield, AWS WAF, AWS SSO, AWS secrets manager)
- Security external network connections to and from the AWS Cloud (e.g. VPN, Direct Connect)

## Determine appropriate data security controls

Knowledge of
- Data Access and governance
- Data recovery
- Data retention and classification
- Encryption and appropriate key management

Skills in
- Aligning AWS technologies to meet compliance requirements
- Encrypting data at rest (e.g. AWS Key management KMS)
- Encrypting data in transit (e.g. AWS Certificate manager ACM using TLS)
- Implementing access policies for encryption keys
- Implementing data backups and replications
- Implementing policies for data access, lifecycle and protection
- Rotating encryption keys and renewing certificates
